# Glaze — OKHST Color Theme Generator

Package: `@tenphi/glaze` — zero-dependency color theme generator built on OKHST (OKHSL with a contrast-uniform **tone** axis), with WCAG + APCA contrast solving for light, dark, and high-contrast schemes.

## Key Features

- OKHST color model — OKHSL rendering substrate with a contrast-uniform `tone` axis (equal tone steps → equal contrast)
- WCAG 2 + APCA contrast solving (automatic tone adjustment)
- Unified dark mode — single `100 − t` tone inversion, no fitted curve
- Multi-scheme generation (light, dark, high-contrast)
- Multi-format output (`okhsl`, `rgb`, `hsl`, `oklch`); `okhst` is input-only
- Import/export (serialize/restore theme, color-token, and palette configs)
- Tree-shakeable ESM + CJS dual-format package
- TypeScript-first with full type definitions

## Project Structure

```
src/
  index.ts                 # Entry point, re-exports everything
  glaze.ts                 # Core theme factory: glaze(), glaze.palette(), glaze.themeFrom(), etc.
  types.ts                 # All TypeScript type definitions
  okhst.ts                 # OKHST tone layer: tone↔lightness transfers, scheme mapping
  okhsl-color-math.ts      # OKHSL/sRGB/OKLab conversions, hex parsing, format functions
  contrast-solver.ts        # Tone-based WCAG + APCA contrast solver
  glaze.test.ts            # Main test suite
  contrast-solver.test.ts  # Contrast solver tests
```

